  "prompt": "Does NASA recruit Indians?",
  "response": "Yes, NASA does recruit individuals from around the world, including Indian citizens, for various positions, especially if they meet the required qualifications and skills. However, there are specific eligibility criteria regarding citizenship for certain roles. Many science, technology, engineering, and mathematics (STEM) positions at NASA may require U.S. citizenship due to the sensitive nature of the work. \n\nInternational candidates, including Indians, may find opportunities through partnerships, internships, or collaborations, particularly in research areas where their expertise is valuable. It's also common for Indian nationals to work with NASA through educational programs or as part of joint research initiatives with universities and institutions that have partnerships with NASA. If you're interested in a specific role, it's best to review the job postings on NASA's official careers website or related portals for more detailed information.",
